<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 13 at 3:55PM MDT  by NWS Saltlake</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of north central Beaver
County through 430 PM MDT...
At 355 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles northwest of Milford. This storm was nearly stationary.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Milford.
This includes Utah Route 21 between mile markers 62 and 79.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
